<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the THREE `sys_choice` rows that
    enumerate the legal values of the `pending_reason` Choice field on the
    `x_[scope]_case` custom table inside the scoped application
    `x_[scope]_case_management`.

    Per AAP Section 0.4.1 (Refactored Structure Planning):
        choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml -> Awaiting Info,
        Awaiting Third Party, Other

    Per AAP Section 0.5.5 (State-Machine Transition Map verbatim):
        From          To           Required condition / behavior
        In Progress   Pending      None; sets pending_reason
                                   (Awaiting Info / Awaiting Third Party / Other)
        Pending       In Progress  None; clears pending_reason

    The forward-slash separator in the AAP transition spec means the
    Pending state requires the user to select EXACTLY ONE of these three
    discriminator values - no other value is permitted. The three records
    below are the EXHAUSTIVE, CLOSED enumeration that the AAP mandates -
    exactly three records, no more and no fewer. Per the MINIMAL CHANGE
    CLAUSE in AAP Section 0.7.2, additional pending reasons such as
    `Awaiting Approval`, `Awaiting Documentation`, `Awaiting Internal
    Review`, `Awaiting Customer Confirmation`, etc. are explicitly out of
    scope for this POC. The increment-of-100 sequence spacing leaves room
    for future extensibility (e.g., inserting `Awaiting Approval` at
    sequence 150 between `Awaiting Info` and `Awaiting Third Party`)
    without renumbering, but no extension is authorized in this build.

    Per AAP Sections 0.5.5, 0.5.2, and 0.4.1, the labels declared here are
    read by:

      The parent dictionary entry that declares this field as Choice:
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_pending_reason.xml
            (declares the column as a Choice via `<choice>3</choice>`,
            optional/non-mandatory at the schema level since `pending_reason`
            is only populated when the case is in the Pending state, and
            cleared by ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
            when the case transitions back to In Progress.)

      The Flow Designer subflow that prompts the user during the
      In Progress -> Pending transition:
        ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml
            (per AAP Section 0.5.5, the subflow has NO blocking-error
            condition - it merely captures the discriminator value via
            a prompt-user step. The prompt's options are exactly the
            three labels declared below: `Awaiting Info`,
            `Awaiting Third Party`, `Other`. If a label here changes,
            the subflow's prompt list MUST change too.)

      The Business Rule that clears this field on the reverse transition:
        ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
            (per AAP Section 0.5.5, when a case transitions
            Pending -> In Progress, the previously-set `pending_reason`
            is cleared - i.e., set to empty string. The rule does NOT
            reference specific labels here; it just clears whatever
            value is currently stored. So adding/removing labels in
            this Choice list does NOT require updating the business
            rule's body, only the subflow's prompt-options list.)

      The synthetic demo cases satisfying AAP Section 0.4.1 minimum-data
      threshold (specifically demo_04, the Pending-state General Inquiry
      case per AAP Section 0.4.1: "x_[scope]_case_demo_04.xml (Pending,
      General Inquiry)"). The seed value MUST match one of the three labels
      declared below byte-for-byte for the GlideRecord seed insert to
      succeed against the parent dictionary's `<choice>3</choice>`
      enforcement.

    Note on the Experience Portal: per AAP Section 0.4.4 the public
    submission form has only five inputs (subject, type, description,
    requester_name, requester_email) and the lookup page returns ONLY
    status/subject/opened_date. The `pending_reason` field is therefore
    NEVER exposed to anonymous external requesters - it is an
    internal-only operational discriminator. The portal cannot create
    cases in the Pending state (anonymous submissions land in `Draft`
    per ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_submit.xml) and
    cannot read `pending_reason` (the lookup widget's whitelist excludes
    it per ../portal/rest/sys_ws_definition_x_[scope]_case_status_lookup.xml).

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java does NOT
        declare a `pending_reason` field. ArkCase's CaseFile.java contains
        only a `status` field (line 141-142):
            @Column(name = "cm_case_status")
            private String status;
        and references `ChangeCaseStatus` (line 199) for transition
        history. There is no separate "pending reason" discriminator.
        ArkCase's actual pending-state reasons - if any - were tracked
        via the free-form Activiti BPMN variables side-channel, custom
        Frevvo form extensions, or Solr `comment` fields, none of which
        are in scope for this POC per AAP Section 0.3.2.

        The ServiceNow target FIXES this gap by introducing an explicit
        `pending_reason` Choice field with a controlled vocabulary of
        EXACTLY three labels here, enforced at platform-validation time
        through the parent dictionary entry's `<choice>3</choice>`
        setting in ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_pending_reason.xml. This
        gives the AAP-required Pending state a structured, queryable
        discriminator that internal users can filter on (e.g., a
        case_manager building a saved query "all cases pending external
        information" filters where `status=Pending AND pending_reason=
        Awaiting Third Party`) without resorting to free-text comment
        scraping.

        This is one of the few intentional ENRICHMENTS the target makes
        relative to the source ArkCase domain model - all other field
        additions are explicitly forbidden per AAP Section 0.7.4
        ("Preserve the user-prompt's data-model field set verbatim ...
        no additions, no renames, no type relaxations"). The
        `pending_reason` field is permitted because it is ITSELF
        AAP-mandated by Section 0.5.5 (its three values are listed
        verbatim in the transition-map row "In Progress -> Pending").

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFileConstants.java
        declares only OBJECT_TYPE, EVENT_TYPE_*, and queue-action
        constants - no pending-reason enumeration. The target therefore
        introduces this enumeration entirely from the AAP, not from any
        ArkCase source.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/ChangeCaseStatus.java
        defines its own status enumeration (IN_APPROVAL, DRAFT, APPROVED)
        which is entirely separate from this `pending_reason` Choice
        list and is OUT OF SCOPE per AAP Section 0.3.2. The target's
        case status enumeration is in ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml
        (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed); the
        `pending_reason` declared here is an ORTHOGONAL discriminator
        that further qualifies the `Pending` status only.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1 and 0.7.2):
      - EXACTLY three records: no fewer, no more. Per AAP Section 0.5.5
        verbatim. The three records below are the COMPLETE enumeration.
      - Title Case labels with single-space separators: `Awaiting Info`,
        `Awaiting Third Party`, `Other`. NOT camelCase (`AwaitingInfo`,
        `AwaitingThirdParty`), NOT kebab-case (`Awaiting-Info`,
        `Awaiting-Third-Party`), NOT lowercase (`awaiting info`), NOT
        snake_case (`awaiting_info`, `awaiting_third_party`). Each label
        is exact AAP-spelling and AAP-casing.
      - `Awaiting Third Party` has THREE words separated by single ASCII
        spaces. Not double spaces, not non-breaking spaces (U+00A0),
        not tab characters - just plain ASCII 0x20.
      - Label = Value pattern: each `<value>` matches its sibling
        `<label>` byte-for-byte. The stored value IS the human-readable
        label - no integer codes, no enum ordinals, no separate
        machine-key. This matches the pattern used by sibling Choice
        lists in this app (sys_choice_case_status, sys_choice_case_type,
        sys_choice_case_priority, sys_choice_case_task_status,
        sys_choice_case_task_type, sys_choice_case_party_party_type)
        and is essential for the Flow Designer subflow's prompt-user
        step to round-trip the selected value back into the GlideRecord
        column without translation, and for any GlideAggregate
        groupBy('pending_reason') queries to produce coherent labels.
      - Sequence ordering matches the AAP Section 0.5.5 listing order
        ("Awaiting Info / Awaiting Third Party / Other") in increments
        of 100:
            Awaiting Info (100) -> Awaiting Third Party (200) -> Other (300)
        This drives:
            (a) the dropdown order on the case form (when the case is
                in Pending status and the field is rendered)
            (b) the prompt-user option order in the Flow Designer subflow
                ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml
            (c) the future extensibility - increment-of-100 spacing leaves
                room for inserting new values (e.g., `Awaiting Approval`
                at sequence 150 between `Awaiting Info` and `Awaiting
                Third Party`) without renumbering existing rows, though
                the AAP MINIMAL CHANGE CLAUSE prohibits adding any in
                this POC.
        Note that "Other" is intentionally LAST per the conventional
        catch-all positioning - it appears at the bottom of the dropdown
        as the fallback selection when none of the specific reasons
        match.
      - All three records are <inactive>false</inactive>: every value is
        active and selectable in the dropdown. There are no deprecated
        legacy values to filter out (this is a greenfield Choice list
        with no source ArkCase analog).
      - No <dependent_value/>: pending_reason is a TOP-LEVEL discriminator
        whose legal values do NOT depend on `type`, `priority`, or any
        other field. A General Inquiry can be Pending for any of the
        three reasons; a Complaint can be Pending for any of the three
        reasons. No cascading dropdown is needed. (The Choice IS implicitly
        "scoped" by status=Pending in that it is only ever populated when
        status=Pending, but that is enforced by the
        ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml subflow and
        the ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
        business rule, not by a `dependent_value` on the Choice records.)
      - No <hint/>: the labels are self-documenting. `Awaiting Info` is
        universally understood as "waiting for additional information
        from the requester or another party"; `Awaiting Third Party` is
        "waiting for an external organization not directly involved in
        the case"; `Other` is the catch-all. The agent prompt explicitly
        suppresses helper text per the POC scope (Key Insight #3:
        "Other is a fallback. The AAP doesn't restrict what Other means;
        the Pending subflow may capture additional details in a future
        enhancement, but for POC, the bare label is sufficient.").
      - No default value at this Choice level: the parent dictionary
        entry ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_pending_reason.xml has an
        empty <default_value/> because the field is null/empty when
        the case is in any status other than Pending. The value is
        explicitly captured by the validate_pending_transition subflow
        at the moment of transition - there is no auto-applied default.
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: every record's `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` resolve into the `x_[scope]_case_management`
        scoped application by `source` attribute lookup. NO global-scope
        writes - the OOB tables sys_user, sys_user_group, sys_user_role,
        core_company, task, incident, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]_case_management`), not by literal sys_id. Each
        record's `<sys_id>` element value is THIS record's own
        deterministic primary key - computed as MD5 of the canonical
        identifier `x_[scope]_case.pending_reason.<Value>` so that
        re-generation of this XML yields byte-identical output (no
        random UUIDs). The sys_id is NOT a reference to any other
        record. The MD5 inputs are documented in the trailing comment
        block below for full traceability.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time, which the import process resolves into the final
        scope namespace.
      - English language only: `<language>en</language>` on every record
        per the POC scope. The platform supports localization via
        additional sys_choice records keyed by `language`, but no
        non-English locales are in scope.
      - `<sys_domain>global</sys_domain>` on every record: domain
        separation is not used by this scoped application.
      - No PII: the labels are categorical waiting-state terms only;
        no real names, email addresses, or organizational identifiers
        are derived from or stored in these records.
      - No smart quotes, no leading/trailing whitespace, no BOM. Strict
        XML conformance for ServiceNow Update Set re-import preview.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      THIS RECORD SET MUST LOAD AFTER:
        - ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml (scoped application)
        - ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml (scope record)
        - ../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml (parent table; pending_reason
          field's host)
        - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_pending_reason.xml (parent
          dictionary entry; declares the column shape, choice=3,
          mandatory=false. Without this entry the sys_choice records
          below have no column to attach to.)

      THIS RECORD SET MUST LOAD BEFORE:
        - ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml
            (the subflow that prompts the user to select one of these
            three values when transitioning In Progress -> Pending. The
            subflow's prompt-user step expects exactly the labels
            defined here.)
        - ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml
            (the business rule that clears this field on the reverse
            transition Pending -> In Progress. The rule does NOT
            reference specific labels but does reference the field
            name `pending_reason`, which depends on the parent
            dictionary entry being loaded - and the dictionary entry's
            choice column type means the sys_choice records here MUST
            be in place before any seed data tries to populate the
            field.)
        - ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_04.xml
            (the Pending-state General Inquiry demo case that exercises
            this Choice field. Per AAP Section 0.4.1, this is the only
            demo case in the Pending state in the seed data set, so
            it MUST set `pending_reason` to one of the three labels
            here byte-for-byte. Other demo cases that are NOT in the
            Pending state leave this field empty.)

      Loading order is enforced by the alphabetical Update Set preview
      ordering plus the record-by-record dependency-resolution pass.

    The MD5 input for each record's <sys_id> is the canonical identifier
    <table>.<element>.<value>, matching the convention used by the
    sibling Choice files (sys_choice_case_status.xml,
    sys_choice_case_type.xml, sys_choice_case_priority.xml,
    sys_choice_case_task_status.xml, sys_choice_case_task_type.xml,
    sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml):
        MD5("x_[scope]_case.pending_reason.Awaiting Info")        = 4c80901f97d80493815d6e5035350545
        MD5("x_[scope]_case.pending_reason.Awaiting Third Party") = f9f1b37a725e88b044b6b7e39c215670
        MD5("x_[scope]_case.pending_reason.Other")                = 6bfddaadc6361fe46d2756027eefec2f
    These hashes are recomputable from the AAP-mandated canonical input,
    guaranteeing deterministic XML re-generation across all build runs and
    idempotent re-imports on any fresh PDI without sys_id collisions.
-->
<unload unload_date="2025-01-01 00:00:00">
